=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect ethyl isonipecotate (ethyl piperidine-4-carboxylate) as the N-Boc carbamate to give N-Boc-ethyl isonipecotate. | Step 2: Deprotonate at C-2 (LDA or LiHMDS) and alkylate with MeI to form N-Boc-ethyl 2-methylpiperidine-4-carboxylate. | Step 3: Saponify the ester (NaOH, then acid workup) to give N-Boc-2-methylpiperidine-4-carboxylic acid. | Step 4: Couple this acid with 2-amino-4-chlorophenol (e.g., via acid chloride/CDI), then cyclodehydrate (POCl3 or PPA) to build the benzoxazole, giving N-Boc-4-(5-chlorobenzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)-2-methylpiperidine. | Step 5: Remove Boc with TFA or HCl/dioxane to furnish the target CC1CCC(c2nc3cc(Cl)ccc3o2)CN1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
Step 1: Protect ethyl isonipecotate (ethyl piperidine-4-carboxylate) as the N-Boc carbamate to give N-Boc-ethyl isonipecotate. | Step 2: Deprotonate at C-2 (LDA or LiHMDS) and alkylate with MeI to form N-Boc-ethyl 2-methylpiperidine-4-carboxylate. | Step 3: Saponify the ester (NaOH, then acid workup) to give N-Boc-2-methylpiperidine-4-carboxylic acid. | Step 4: Couple this acid with 2-amino-4-chlorophenol (e.g., via acid chloride/CDI), then cyclodehydrate (POCl3 or PPA) to build the benzoxazole, giving N-Boc-4-(5-chlorobenzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)-2-methylpiperidine. | Step 5: Remove Boc with TFA or HCl/dioxane to furnish the target CC1CCC(c2nc3cc(Cl)ccc3o2)CN1.

